---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="About me" description="A short bio of Filippo Carmenati.">
  <style is:global>
    main .about-heading { font-size: 36px; font-weight: 700; margin: 0 0 1.5rem; }
    main p { font-size: 18px; }
  </style>

  <h1 class="about-heading">About me</h1>

  <p>
    I am a lively boy who strives to bring the two hemispheres of his brain
    into peaceful harmony.
  </p>

  <p>
    Curious and restless from childhood, I feel I started having an interest
    in science from an early age, when, at five years old, I started making
    small experiments - playing with lizards’ tails or with water and
    toothpaste, freezing it in a bottle and saying to my mother:
    “That’s the experiment!”
  </p>

  <p>
    Many were the things I wanted to become (probably driven by a mix of
    curiosity for both the subject and the unusual name): a
    <a
      href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paleoanthropology"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer"
    >paleoanthropologist</a>, a
    <a
      href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Musicology"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer"
    >musicologist</a>, an orchestra’s director and a basketball player.
  </p>

  <p>
    I ended up studying agricultural sciences, given the indecision between
    a scientific and a humanities subject. Fortunately, even after 12 years
    of studying, the more I immerse myself into this field the more I
    realise its beauty and transversality across areas.
  </p>

  <p>
    With time, I understood that my calling is in finding meaning in things,
    answering the questions I ask myself. Asking questions, seeking answers,
    and sharing this pleasure in knowledge to help others see the beauty that
    surrounds us feels like one of my ways to be happy.
  </p>

  <p>
    I like writing, and I feel this is my way of expression - which is also
    the main reason why I created this space. An “island” for sharing, with
    the ones interested, parts of what I spontaneously write in my diaries,
    and a way to reach out to me.
  </p>

  <p>
    If I had to describe myself with three adjectives: unmercifully lucky,
    tremendously curious, filled with passion.
  </p>

  <p>
    Here is the list of <a href="/rubricas/lost-mentors">mentors I have never
    had</a>.
  </p>
</BaseLayout>
